WEBVTT

00:03.003 --> 00:03.570
(Mike)
Graceland...

00:06.139 --> 00:07.140
You all right?

00:07.140 --> 00:08.275
I need your help.

00:08.275 --> 00:09.610
This is going to be
the hardest thing

00:09.643 --> 00:11.245
you have ever done
in your life, Mike.

00:11.278 --> 00:12.746
Oh.

00:12.980 --> 00:13.981
Ohh!

00:14.014 --> 00:15.215
[screaming]

00:15.249 --> 00:17.117
God damn it!

00:17.150 --> 00:18.285
(Charlie)
I want Germaine.

00:18.318 --> 00:19.486
He tries to bolt,
don't be afraid

00:19.520 --> 00:20.687
to kick his ass through a door.

00:20.687 --> 00:22.122
Copy that.

00:22.155 --> 00:24.157
Somebody want to tell me
what the hell happened?

00:24.157 --> 00:25.392
He's an informant.

00:25.425 --> 00:26.527
(Jakes)
He's an informant for whom?

00:26.560 --> 00:28.028
(Charlie)
ATF.

00:28.061 --> 00:30.130
If we bring Ari in now,
we can't touch Martun.

00:30.163 --> 00:31.298
I want Martun.

00:31.298 --> 00:32.699
I need you two to stay tied
to Toros.

00:32.733 --> 00:36.203
Johnny, Briggs didn't want us
here to watch Toros.

00:36.236 --> 00:39.373
He wanted us here
so we wouldn't watch him.

00:39.406 --> 00:42.576
Who else are you hiding
in our organization?

00:42.576 --> 00:43.577
No one.

00:43.577 --> 00:45.112
Aaah!

00:45.145 --> 00:46.547
Spit it out.

00:46.580 --> 00:49.383
The DEA. Paige Arkin.
That's her name.

00:49.416 --> 00:50.984
You need to go.

00:51.018 --> 00:52.452
It's less than an hour
to the ceremony.

00:52.486 --> 00:55.622
Tevan Adamian knows you're DEA.
Soon, Toros is going to know.

00:58.725 --> 01:01.995
You gonna let me in, or you
want to play more mind games?

01:02.029 --> 01:03.730
You've got to trust me.

01:03.730 --> 01:06.333
Don't talk to me about trust.

01:06.366 --> 01:08.168
You're bullshitting me.

01:08.168 --> 01:10.337
[Paige screams]

01:16.677 --> 01:19.646
[classical music playing]

01:19.680 --> 01:27.688
♪ ♪

01:31.325 --> 01:34.294
[choir singing]

01:34.328 --> 01:42.302
♪ ♪

04:27.334 --> 04:28.568
You know, you're so
full of shit,

04:28.602 --> 04:30.070
and everybody here knows it.

04:30.103 --> 04:31.438
Is that right?

04:31.471 --> 04:33.073
Is that what you know, Johnny,
that I'm full of shit?

04:33.073 --> 04:35.175
Chill, okay, look, I don't want
to be in the middle of this.

04:35.208 --> 04:36.476
We're all in the middle of this.

04:36.510 --> 04:38.745
What Paige did was self-defense,
but instead we cleaned it up

04:38.745 --> 04:40.480
to keep your cover intact.

04:40.514 --> 04:42.682
Okay. Well, what would you
like to do, Mike?

04:42.716 --> 04:44.017
Do you want to report it?

04:44.050 --> 04:45.485
You want to burn Paige
and the house?

04:45.519 --> 04:47.454
This isn't about the house,
okay?

04:47.487 --> 04:49.222
And if you're so concerned
about Paige,

04:49.256 --> 04:50.624
maybe you shouldn't have
let Logan burn her.

04:50.657 --> 04:53.226
Logan was being
tortured, Mike.

04:53.260 --> 04:54.628
And Paige, who happens
to be my friend,

04:54.661 --> 04:56.396
was putting herself
in harms' way to--

04:56.429 --> 04:58.265
Even right now, he's playing
an angle. Do you not see this?

04:58.298 --> 05:01.501
(Paige)
He's right. He's right.

05:01.501 --> 05:04.104
The moment my name left
Logan's lips,

05:04.104 --> 05:05.605
Briggs called me.

05:05.639 --> 05:07.507
And the only reason
why I was in danger

05:07.507 --> 05:09.576
is because you two
weren't there.

05:09.609 --> 05:11.344
They're not wrong, Mike.

05:11.378 --> 05:14.114
If we would have just done
what he said...

05:14.114 --> 05:15.649
I'm done listening
to anything he says.

05:15.649 --> 05:19.986
If he's playing an angle,
what angle is that?

05:21.388 --> 05:24.124
I don't know.

05:24.157 --> 05:26.126
I know something, Mike.

05:26.126 --> 05:28.595
I know that when you wanted to
leave a canister of sarin gas

05:28.628 --> 05:31.565
in the back of a Pontiac GTO,

05:31.565 --> 05:34.134
the whole house trusted you,
didn't we?

05:34.167 --> 05:36.536
Now you don't have to trust me.
You don't have to respect me.

05:36.536 --> 05:37.671
I really could give a shit.

05:37.671 --> 05:40.073
But before you start
pointing fingers at me,

05:40.106 --> 05:43.343
you might want
to take a look at yourself.

05:57.290 --> 06:00.260
[electronic music]

06:00.293 --> 06:07.634
♪ ♪

06:13.006 --> 06:17.110
♪ ♪

06:17.143 --> 06:19.312
Friend of mine recommended
a place over on Washington.

06:19.312 --> 06:21.147
I wasn't sure what you like
so I got some powdered,

06:21.181 --> 06:22.415
jelly-filled, some crullers--

06:22.449 --> 06:23.683
Is this an apology?

06:23.717 --> 06:26.586
When we met,
I wasn't at my best.

06:26.586 --> 06:29.322
Sent over the files
on Germaine Marsden.

06:29.322 --> 06:30.590
If you read them,
you'll understand why--

06:30.590 --> 06:33.193
I know what he did to you,
Agent DeMarco.

06:33.226 --> 06:34.728
I've seen the reports.

06:34.728 --> 06:36.129
I've seen the medical.

06:36.162 --> 06:38.331
As a woman, I'd love
to see him fry.

06:38.365 --> 06:40.967
And as an agent?

06:41.001 --> 06:44.237
When we captured Germaine,
it was a big win for ATF.

06:44.271 --> 06:46.706
Not because we're interested
in money launderers. We're not.

06:46.706 --> 06:49.709
But because one of his clients
is way up on our wish list.

06:49.743 --> 06:51.244
A big fish gun runner.

06:51.278 --> 06:54.147
Germaine was happy to sell
his client down the river.

06:54.180 --> 06:55.715
So we made him a deal.

06:55.749 --> 06:57.584
But before we made our bust,
our big fish here

06:57.617 --> 07:00.353
introduced Germaine
to a couple smaller guppies.

07:00.387 --> 07:04.457
Word of mouth spreads, his new
clients drew newer clients.

07:04.491 --> 07:06.493
A year later,
I'm looking at a network

07:06.493 --> 07:10.463
of 41 gun runners
in 22 countries and growing.

07:10.497 --> 07:12.432
Like flies to honey.

07:12.465 --> 07:14.534
Like flies to shit.

07:14.567 --> 07:17.037
Either way, their money
flows through Germaine.

07:17.070 --> 07:19.072
I see where it comes from,
I see where it goes to,

07:19.105 --> 07:21.741
I see which Mideast charities
these assholes support.

07:21.975 --> 07:24.744
So, to answer your question,
as an agent,

07:24.744 --> 07:26.479
I don't give a damn about you.

07:26.513 --> 07:28.481
Think I like you better
as a woman.

07:28.481 --> 07:32.485
Listen, I know how this case
is important to you.

07:32.485 --> 07:34.354
Just promise me you'll get me
Germaine when you're done.

07:34.387 --> 07:36.222
Respectfully, Agent DeMarco,

07:36.256 --> 07:38.358
I don't have to promise you
a Goddamn thing.

07:41.127 --> 07:42.629
(Charlie)
Yeah, I brought this bitch
a box of doughnuts,

07:42.662 --> 07:44.230
she tells me to go to hell.

07:44.264 --> 07:45.498
I swear to God,
people think their shit

07:45.532 --> 07:46.599
is the only shit that matters.

07:46.633 --> 07:48.101
Yeah, imagine that.

07:48.134 --> 07:50.103
So Stanwood don't play ball.
What's going on now?

07:50.136 --> 07:51.237
No, but I got something.

07:51.271 --> 07:53.239
Germaine's got
a master of weak ties.

07:53.239 --> 07:54.507
What's that?

07:54.541 --> 07:56.710
It's a model for representing
social connections.

07:56.743 --> 07:59.112
You learn all types of shit
at Quantico.

07:59.145 --> 08:01.114
So these guys here,
they don't know each other.

08:01.114 --> 08:02.248
They're linked together
by weak ties,

08:02.248 --> 08:03.350
'cause they each have
a relationship

08:03.383 --> 08:04.651
with the guy in the middle.

08:04.651 --> 08:05.719
The master of weak ties.

08:05.752 --> 08:07.120
You steal his ass
from Germaine,

08:07.153 --> 08:09.522
the rest of ATF's targets
come tumbling down.

08:09.556 --> 08:11.324
But look, what I need
you to do is I need you

08:11.358 --> 08:12.659
to convince Germaine
to set up a meet and greet

08:12.692 --> 08:13.660
with his top clients.

08:13.693 --> 08:14.661
- A meet and greet.
- Yeah.

08:14.694 --> 08:16.229
Might be tough, Charlie.

08:16.262 --> 08:18.298
I've only been under
with the guy a few days.

08:18.298 --> 08:20.100
He has me half-naked
busting down drywall,

08:20.133 --> 08:21.134
making delivery runs.

08:21.167 --> 08:22.502
I think a meet and greet
with his top clients

08:22.535 --> 08:23.970
might be a little premature.

08:24.004 --> 08:25.271
Well, then you're gonna have
to speed up the timeline.

08:25.305 --> 08:27.007
Listen, we've been doing
this for a minute now.

08:27.007 --> 08:28.475
- We can't slow down.
- I'll try.

08:28.508 --> 08:30.276
No, don't try.
Do your job, Dale.

08:30.310 --> 08:32.679
Listen, even if Germaine
goes for it,

08:32.679 --> 08:34.114
it's going to take
at least a few days to set up.

08:34.147 --> 08:35.148
That's fine. I can--

08:35.148 --> 08:36.649
You can go home.

08:36.683 --> 08:38.685
You can go home, Charlie.

08:38.685 --> 08:41.554
You're tired.
And you look like ass.

08:41.588 --> 08:44.991
Wow. And you're still single.

08:45.025 --> 08:46.559
And I'm going to tell you
as a friend,

08:46.559 --> 08:48.695
you got to talk to Briggs.

08:48.728 --> 08:51.998
He deserves to know--
don't give me that face.

08:52.032 --> 08:57.203
And this baby and this case,
you can't carry it on your own.

09:01.674 --> 09:03.710
Ceremony was nice.

09:03.710 --> 09:06.713
Uncle Tev and Martun
were there.

09:06.713 --> 09:09.182
Lot of weeping old ladies.

09:09.215 --> 09:12.018
Huge platter of goat matagh.

09:12.052 --> 09:13.319
Was beautiful.

09:13.353 --> 09:16.723
You should have come.

09:16.723 --> 09:18.691
Somebody had to take care
of that body.

09:18.725 --> 09:23.063
Ah, yes. FBI bigwig Logan.

09:23.063 --> 09:25.065
Where you dump that trash?

09:25.065 --> 09:29.569
Long drop off a tall pier.

09:29.569 --> 09:32.172
Then I guess today
is housecleaning day.

09:32.205 --> 09:36.042
My manager found Toros
out there this morning.

09:36.042 --> 09:37.310
What are you talking about,
he came here to hide?

09:37.310 --> 09:39.245
He came her to die,
the idiot.

09:39.279 --> 09:40.480
Write a long suicide note

09:40.480 --> 09:42.215
like he thinks he's
some kind of poet.

09:42.248 --> 09:45.752
Slit his own throat
and bled out on my couch.

09:45.752 --> 09:47.353
Wow.

09:47.353 --> 09:50.223
Well, where do we celebrate?

09:50.223 --> 09:52.158
No time for parties, man.

09:52.192 --> 09:54.194
Martun is anxious for me
to get the tattooing done

09:54.227 --> 09:56.429
because Uncle Tev is dying.

09:56.463 --> 09:58.064
I'm sorry to hear that.

09:58.098 --> 10:01.034
This kidney we got him saved his
life and now it's killing him.

10:01.067 --> 10:02.602
It's ironic and very sad.

10:02.635 --> 10:04.204
But it means
now we got to start

10:04.237 --> 10:06.072
meeting with
all of these idiots.

10:06.106 --> 10:10.276
Here we got every wannabe
gangster for three counties.

10:10.310 --> 10:12.745
We got to do
a little handshake tour.

10:12.745 --> 10:14.147
Mm.

10:14.180 --> 10:15.748
I want you to learn
the name of every gang

10:15.982 --> 10:18.318
and the name of every player.

10:18.351 --> 10:19.752
You want me to memorize
all of that.

10:19.752 --> 10:21.321
The higher you get,

10:21.354 --> 10:23.756
the more you've got to
start using your brain.

10:23.990 --> 10:27.193
You're not going to see
the king out there

10:27.227 --> 10:29.529
plowing the fields,
are you?

10:29.562 --> 10:32.532
[upbeat guitar music]

10:32.565 --> 10:39.105
♪ ♪

10:39.105 --> 10:41.241
[sighs]

10:41.274 --> 10:48.515
♪ ♪

10:48.548 --> 10:52.252
- Hey.
- Hey yourself.

10:52.252 --> 10:53.620
Let me ask you
a question, man,

10:53.653 --> 10:56.256
and please just
be real with me.

10:56.289 --> 10:58.258
Yeah, man, always.
What's up?

10:58.258 --> 11:00.360
What the hell's going on?

11:00.393 --> 11:02.362
I didn't want to say anything
in front of everybody else,

11:02.395 --> 11:06.299
but I don't blame Mike for
cracking up over all of this.

11:06.332 --> 11:09.135
All this shit with
the Sarkissians is just...

11:09.169 --> 11:10.737
It feels wrong.

11:10.970 --> 11:14.407
Yeah, Johnny, it's all kinds
of wrong, you know?

11:14.440 --> 11:16.509
I feel like I'm walking on tar.

11:16.543 --> 11:20.013
Every time I try to pull out
a leg, I just sink in deeper.

11:20.013 --> 11:22.382
Mm-hmm.

11:22.415 --> 11:24.017
Well, man, you know if you
got something in the works

11:24.050 --> 11:26.085
you could just
tell me, right?

11:26.119 --> 11:28.221
I always got your back.

11:28.254 --> 11:29.689
I know that,
and I appreciate it,

11:29.689 --> 11:32.158
but there's nothing
in the works, okay?

11:32.158 --> 11:33.560
Nothing but work.

11:33.560 --> 11:35.562
If there was, I'd tell you.

11:35.562 --> 11:38.665
Just a bad
situation then, huh?

11:38.698 --> 11:43.136
Yeah, it's a grip of bad
situations, but you know what?

11:43.169 --> 11:44.404
Now's the endgame.

11:44.404 --> 11:46.439
Tevan Adamian's
on his last legs,

11:46.439 --> 11:48.675
I'm set up
as Ari's right hand.

11:48.708 --> 11:50.443
You know, it's been a bitch
but if this is what it takes

11:50.476 --> 11:52.178
to get Martun
after everything he's done,

11:52.212 --> 11:54.380
I'll walk through the fire.

11:54.414 --> 11:55.715
You need some help?

11:55.748 --> 11:57.383
No. No, I'm good.

11:57.417 --> 12:00.420
But if I do, you'll be
the first one I call.

12:00.453 --> 12:02.188
All right.

12:02.222 --> 12:06.192
Just--just be good,
all right?

12:06.192 --> 12:09.028
Yeah, I'll try.

12:15.568 --> 12:18.471
Soto.

12:22.709 --> 12:25.712
[rock music]

12:25.712 --> 12:33.753
♪ ♪

12:44.130 --> 12:47.100
[children playing]

12:47.133 --> 12:55.141
♪ ♪

13:03.082 --> 13:03.659
[rock music]

13:05.718 --> 13:11.991
♪ ♪

13:11.991 --> 13:14.260
You disappear.

13:14.260 --> 13:15.595
Madison thought you were
gone for good.

13:15.628 --> 13:17.664
She was upset.

13:17.664 --> 13:19.465
Hey, you were right, man.

13:19.499 --> 13:22.068
I had to get cleaned up.

13:22.101 --> 13:23.503
So you're clean? That's it?

13:23.536 --> 13:26.306
Yeah.

13:26.339 --> 13:28.107
How you feeling?

13:28.107 --> 13:30.376
I'm feeling like I got
shot with a bullet.

13:30.410 --> 13:31.477
Maybe she's awake,
I don't know.

13:31.511 --> 13:34.247
I didn't come to see Madison.

13:34.247 --> 13:36.182
I took a look in an atlas.

13:36.215 --> 13:39.218
Bali's 9,000 miles away
from Los Angeles.

13:39.252 --> 13:44.090
That's 1/3 of the way
around the world.

13:44.123 --> 13:48.227
Did you really come all this way
just to go home with nothing?

13:48.261 --> 13:50.296
I don't have nothing
but I have dignity.

13:50.296 --> 13:51.431
Vin.

13:51.464 --> 13:53.132
It's not Vin.
It's Gusti.

13:53.166 --> 13:56.969
Why don't you go visit
the mess you leave behind, huh?

13:59.272 --> 14:01.374
[door closes]

14:06.012 --> 14:09.148
Oh, my God.

14:09.182 --> 14:12.018
Hey, Madison.

14:13.686 --> 14:15.688
Mike.

14:15.688 --> 14:18.024
Look at you.

14:18.057 --> 14:20.660
You shaved.

14:20.693 --> 14:24.530
I miss the scruff, but...

14:24.564 --> 14:25.565
Come in here, close the door.

14:25.565 --> 14:28.334
I have something to show you.

14:28.368 --> 14:31.337
It's amazing.

14:36.576 --> 14:38.144
I can't.

14:38.177 --> 14:41.047
It's not heroin or drugs
or anything. It's morphine.

14:41.080 --> 14:43.649
No, I'm saying I can't.

14:43.683 --> 14:45.585
I'm clean.

14:45.585 --> 14:49.389
Damn.

14:49.422 --> 14:51.724
You must be
real proud of yourself.

14:56.329 --> 14:58.197
Just get out.

14:58.197 --> 14:59.465
It was hard.

14:59.465 --> 15:02.668
It was the hardest thing
I've ever done.

15:02.702 --> 15:06.672
But it was worth it.

15:06.706 --> 15:08.541
I feel like myself again.

15:08.574 --> 15:13.312
You know, you're like
a role model, Mike.

15:13.312 --> 15:16.983
You're like that guy,
what's-his-name.

15:20.186 --> 15:23.022
Smokey the Bear.

15:23.055 --> 15:25.324
Only you can
prevent forest fires.

15:25.358 --> 15:30.029
All I'm saying is, you can
do this too if you want.

15:30.062 --> 15:32.498
Spare me the condescension,
Mike.

15:32.498 --> 15:34.767
You're better than this.

15:34.967 --> 15:38.337
You know,
you don't even know me.

15:38.371 --> 15:41.140
You're not my friend.

15:41.174 --> 15:43.209
Just get out.
Just go, all right?

15:43.209 --> 15:45.011
Just get out!

15:45.044 --> 15:47.447
Stupid pussy.

15:47.480 --> 15:50.583
You asshole junkie loser!

16:16.242 --> 16:20.112
I just thought I could keep
running and running, you know?

16:20.112 --> 16:22.081
I'd come home,
I'd have it all figured out.

16:22.114 --> 16:23.082
You and the baby.

16:23.115 --> 16:25.518
But instead, I...

16:28.387 --> 16:32.525
I never should have
lied to you, Paul.

16:32.558 --> 16:35.661
But I just felt cornered

16:35.661 --> 16:38.197
by you, by all of it.

16:43.002 --> 16:45.204
Please say something.

16:49.976 --> 16:53.346
Why are you telling me this?

16:53.379 --> 16:54.547
What?

16:54.580 --> 16:59.218
Why, after all this time...

16:59.252 --> 17:02.688
are you telling me
any of this?

17:02.688 --> 17:06.092
I--I already mourned
our baby.

17:06.125 --> 17:07.126
I thought you'd want to know.

17:07.159 --> 17:08.561
I'm barely above water.

17:08.561 --> 17:11.163
This isn't about us.

17:11.163 --> 17:14.600
[sighs]

17:19.438 --> 17:20.573
I'm sorry.

17:20.606 --> 17:23.376
I'm so sorry.

17:25.344 --> 17:29.181
I should have
been there for you.

17:29.181 --> 17:34.053
I didn't know.

17:34.053 --> 17:36.689
I didn't come in here
to hurt you.

17:36.722 --> 17:40.293
I came in here because
you're my best friend,

17:40.326 --> 17:44.163
and I--

17:44.196 --> 17:47.333
I'm tired of lying.

17:47.333 --> 17:50.102
So tired.

18:03.616 --> 18:06.085
[door closes]

18:06.085 --> 18:09.088
[man speaking Spanish
on television]

18:52.264 --> 18:53.766
Goal!

18:54.000 --> 18:58.437
[woman moans]

19:02.274 --> 19:05.378
[knock on door]

19:05.378 --> 19:07.647
[exhales]

19:07.647 --> 19:09.115
Somebody's at the door.

19:09.115 --> 19:12.118
Oh, don't worry.
He'll go away.

19:12.151 --> 19:14.153
[loud, forceful bangs on door]

19:15.988 --> 19:18.758
[banging on door]

19:18.991 --> 19:22.762
Doesn't sound like
he's going away.

19:22.995 --> 19:26.098
Give me a sec.

19:28.634 --> 19:31.137
Maybe I should go, huh?

19:31.137 --> 19:33.572
No. You stay.

19:39.979 --> 19:41.647
Hey. What the hell
took so long?

19:41.681 --> 19:43.983
What took so long?
It's 3:00 A.M.

19:44.016 --> 19:45.384
No shit, it's 3:00 A.M.

19:45.418 --> 19:47.987
No, you don't just roll up
in here like you own the place.

19:48.020 --> 19:50.156
I pay your rent, Eva.

19:50.189 --> 19:51.524
I don't need
your stupid rent money.

19:51.557 --> 19:54.026
I don't need it.
I don't need you.

19:54.026 --> 19:54.994
[squeaky window opening]

19:55.027 --> 19:56.162
Who's in there?

19:56.162 --> 19:57.997
No one. It's just me.
Go home, Javi.

19:58.030 --> 19:59.398
- Tell me the truth.
- Get out out of here!

19:59.432 --> 20:02.234
Javi! Goddamn it.

20:02.268 --> 20:03.269
- Stop, stop!
- Hey!

20:03.269 --> 20:05.337
[gunfire]

20:05.371 --> 20:08.407
[Latin music on radio]

20:16.115 --> 20:16.561
[Latin music]

20:19.085 --> 20:22.154
♪ ♪

20:22.188 --> 20:23.422
(Germaine)
While I'm gone you give us
a call on the sat phone.

20:23.456 --> 20:24.724
Anything else, you're sacked.

20:24.724 --> 20:26.459
My clients call you
if they need you.

20:26.459 --> 20:29.729
You call them, you're sacked.
And if one dollar goes missing--

20:29.762 --> 20:30.996
I'm sacked.

20:31.030 --> 20:32.331
Yeah.

20:32.331 --> 20:34.333
No, you're dead.
You clear?

20:34.366 --> 20:35.568
Sure, Germaine.
Listen, man.

20:35.568 --> 20:38.437
You can't leave town yet.

20:38.471 --> 20:39.672
Sorry?

20:39.705 --> 20:41.006
Wasn't it you making
all that noise

20:41.040 --> 20:42.541
