on U.S. soil?

20:42.575 --> 20:44.310
That was your whole pitch.

20:44.310 --> 20:46.312
How you telling me
now I can't go, son?

20:46.312 --> 20:48.180
You saw how Swiggy
looked at me.

20:48.214 --> 20:51.050
Like I was the frickin' help
and his name is Swiggy.

20:51.083 --> 20:52.585
I can't imagine he's
your highest-end client.

20:52.618 --> 20:55.087
All I'm saying is that if these
guys are going to respect me,

20:55.087 --> 20:56.422
they need to meet me
standing next to you.

20:56.455 --> 21:00.192
They meet me in some cash house
all sweaty in cover-alls,

21:00.226 --> 21:01.494
they're going to look at me
like I'm a pack animal.

21:01.527 --> 21:02.762
Your whole job

21:02.995 --> 21:04.630
is to move money from
one place to another place.

21:04.663 --> 21:06.465
You are a pack animal.
You're a donkey.

21:06.499 --> 21:08.467
All right. Throw me to the
wolves, it's your prerogative.

21:08.501 --> 21:09.735
Absolutely.

21:09.735 --> 21:11.003
But don't you think
your clients want to know

21:11.036 --> 21:12.271
that they're in good hands?

21:12.304 --> 21:13.672
That when their money
gets dropped off

21:13.706 --> 21:15.708
in some split-level
in Coconut Grove,

21:15.741 --> 21:18.010
Germaine Marsden's approval
is all over the project,

21:18.043 --> 21:21.747
'cause I know I would.

21:21.981 --> 21:25.618
I'm beginning to remember
why I work alone.

21:25.618 --> 21:29.455
What exactly
are you suggesting?

21:33.292 --> 21:34.660
I'm telling you, guy,
this is the worst.

21:34.693 --> 21:36.529
You spend years
trying to get to the top,

21:36.529 --> 21:37.997
then you got to
lower yourself down

21:37.997 --> 21:40.599
and plant a fat kiss
on some guy's ass.

21:40.633 --> 21:42.368
Aw, come on man, it's not like
you're going door to door, man.

21:42.368 --> 21:44.103
These guys are coming to you.

21:44.103 --> 21:45.471
Men with power.

21:45.504 --> 21:49.074
What power? What these guys
got is shit for brains.

21:49.108 --> 21:52.611
The blacks in blue buying guns
to kill the blacks in red,

21:52.645 --> 21:55.381
the Koreans hate the Chinese,
Mexicans, Salvadorians.

21:55.414 --> 21:56.515
What's even the difference

21:56.549 --> 21:58.184
between a Mexican
and a Salvadorian?

21:58.217 --> 22:00.386
I don't know.
Who cares, who cares?

22:00.419 --> 22:01.987
You know, let them
shoot themselves.

22:01.987 --> 22:03.255
Let them shoot
each other, you know?

22:03.255 --> 22:06.225
As long as they're using
Sarkissian steel, right?

22:06.258 --> 22:07.760
Ah, look.
More asses to kiss.

22:07.993 --> 22:09.128
Pucker up.

22:09.128 --> 22:10.996
Soto Street Vatos,
you must be Javier.

22:11.030 --> 22:13.666
My uncle says very nice things
about your mother.

22:17.403 --> 22:19.405
What the hell is this fool
doing here?

22:19.405 --> 22:21.006
Oh.

22:21.006 --> 22:23.142
Hey, brother, man, that was just
a misunderstanding last night.

22:23.142 --> 22:25.277
Shut your face, fool.

22:25.277 --> 22:26.278
What's this about?

22:26.278 --> 22:27.513
What, are you acting
like she even want

22:27.546 --> 22:31.684
your fronting punk-ass wannabe
gang-banger bullshit?

22:31.684 --> 22:33.385
What, do you want to step to me
or something, little man?

22:33.419 --> 22:35.754
Little man.

22:35.988 --> 22:37.022
Bring it, puto.

22:37.022 --> 22:39.291
Lick my balls, mayate.

22:39.291 --> 22:42.161
See? Now you done
messed up real good.

22:42.194 --> 22:43.495
Come on, you want to die today?

22:43.529 --> 22:46.131
You're going to disrespect me,
huh, just like that?

22:46.165 --> 22:48.033
Is that right?

22:48.067 --> 22:51.003
Ari, I'm telling you, you were
lucky we're in your hood.

22:51.003 --> 22:52.271
Lucky? I'm not lucky.

22:52.304 --> 22:55.407
I gotta blow your burrito
all over my brand-new rug.

22:55.441 --> 22:59.011
Javi. Why don't we just
put the guns away?

22:59.044 --> 23:02.681
It's just puss, right?
Plus, you're outnumbered.

23:05.618 --> 23:08.053
Shit. You better
watch your ass.

23:08.053 --> 23:10.456
From here on out, Adamian.

23:10.456 --> 23:12.191
I don't forget shit.

23:12.224 --> 23:15.728
You better not forget,
asshole.

23:15.728 --> 23:20.299
[speaking Spanish]

23:20.332 --> 23:22.101
Let's roll.

23:28.474 --> 23:30.476
[door closes]

23:33.445 --> 23:37.750
What in the Sam Hell
was that about, huh?

23:37.750 --> 23:40.619
I, uh, I may have gone home

23:40.653 --> 23:43.322
with the wrong girl
last night.

23:43.355 --> 23:47.359
[laughs]

23:47.393 --> 23:50.462
You pork his girlfriend?

23:50.496 --> 23:52.498
Ari, I'm really happy
that you're amused,

23:52.531 --> 23:54.233
but did you see that?

23:54.233 --> 23:56.135
That guy is gonna come back
for me, no joke.

23:56.168 --> 23:59.071
Buddy, you're with us now.

23:59.104 --> 24:02.174
If that clown so much as
look at you funny,

24:02.207 --> 24:06.178
I bury him
and his whole family.

24:06.211 --> 24:09.181
[blues music playing]

24:09.214 --> 24:13.719
♪ ♪

24:13.752 --> 24:15.721
- Hey, trouble.
- Hey.

24:15.988 --> 24:18.090
Hey man, you said
you wanted to help out.

24:18.123 --> 24:20.192
Do you know
the Soto Street Vatos?

24:20.225 --> 24:22.661
Yeah.
Yeah, the Sureño set, right?

24:22.661 --> 24:23.729
- Yeah.
- Out of East L.A.?

24:23.762 --> 24:24.997
- Mm-hmm.
- What's up?

24:24.997 --> 24:26.665
Well, uh, as of today

24:26.665 --> 24:29.335
they are at war with the
Sarkissians and it's my fault.

24:29.368 --> 24:32.571
One of the top dogs in
Soto Street is Javi Arrebuena.

24:32.604 --> 24:34.340
I thought if I got close
to his girl,

24:34.373 --> 24:36.976
maybe I could siphon
some intel, pass Ari a dime,

24:37.009 --> 24:38.243
you know, help him get
a leg up on these guys.

24:38.243 --> 24:40.646
Wait, wait, get close
to his girl?

24:40.679 --> 24:44.483
What's that mean?

24:44.516 --> 24:46.618
[laughs]

24:46.652 --> 24:48.120
So you sleep with some girl

24:48.120 --> 24:49.722
and start a goddamn
gang war, man, really?

24:49.755 --> 24:51.357
Yeah, well now the beef's
a lot bigger than me.

24:51.390 --> 24:53.092
Ari's talking about
pre-emptive strikes and shit,

24:53.125 --> 24:54.460
man, it's crazy.

24:54.493 --> 24:57.262
Shit, well, man, at least
that means he likes you, right?

24:57.262 --> 24:58.764
Yeah.

24:58.998 --> 25:01.033
You know, Johnny,
I'm so close to getting Martun.

25:01.033 --> 25:02.634
I just can't afford to have
Ari get got out on the street

25:02.668 --> 25:04.636
by some bangers over
a petty rivalry, you know?

25:04.670 --> 25:07.673
This dude Javi,
the file says he's a boxer.

25:07.706 --> 25:09.141
Yeah. You know,

25:09.141 --> 25:10.509
you're a well-known
pugilist in these parts--

25:10.542 --> 25:15.114
Hey. Yeah. Shit, I could
definitely do this, man.

25:15.147 --> 25:16.348
Yeah, I'll get in it
with them.

25:16.382 --> 25:17.750
See if they're looking
to make a move on you.

25:17.983 --> 25:19.551
I appreciate you, Johnny. You
know, I can't do it all myself.

25:19.551 --> 25:21.387
Sure.
Hey, yo, Briggs.

25:21.420 --> 25:23.422
Yeah.

25:23.422 --> 25:26.158
Thanks for being
up front with me, man.

25:26.191 --> 25:27.693
Yeah.

25:35.067 --> 25:36.954
Soto Street, they're kind of
a rough crew, huh?

25:38.370 --> 25:40.572
Yeah. They're Mafioso crazy.

25:40.606 --> 25:42.541
Cutting off heads and shit.

25:42.574 --> 25:44.576
Still run by that old lady?
Going under with her?

25:44.576 --> 25:47.179
No, no, her son.

25:47.179 --> 25:49.148
Dude thinks he's a fighter.

25:49.181 --> 25:52.184
You think you're going to
be able to hold your own?

25:52.217 --> 25:54.720
Can I hold my own? Is that--
did you really just ask me that?

25:54.753 --> 25:55.587
Yeah.

25:55.621 --> 25:58.057
You think this just happens?

25:58.090 --> 25:59.458
I mean, by chance?
By accident?

25:59.458 --> 26:00.726
Yeah.

26:00.726 --> 26:02.327
Yeah? Dick.

26:02.327 --> 26:06.265
Get your ass in here, man.
You up.

26:06.298 --> 26:10.536
So how you doing?
With everything?

26:10.569 --> 26:13.038
I'm just--I'm just saying,
put somebody down like that,

26:13.072 --> 26:16.241
I know how it is.

26:16.275 --> 26:17.576
Wasn't tactical.

26:17.609 --> 26:20.412
It's not like I double-tapped
him center mass.

26:20.446 --> 26:24.316
One minute he's breathing,
the next minute he's not.

26:24.349 --> 26:27.486
You have no idea
what it's like.

26:32.758 --> 26:35.627
What?

26:35.661 --> 26:38.764
Let me tell you
about Sid Markham.

26:38.997 --> 26:40.265
I killed him.

26:43.202 --> 26:44.603
This is wrong, Johnny.

26:44.603 --> 26:46.038
This is so wrong.

26:46.071 --> 26:49.074
We are not supposed to be
executioners.

26:49.108 --> 26:52.344
I know.

26:52.344 --> 26:54.046
You know, man, we...

26:54.079 --> 26:58.750
we go under with the worst
of the worst, right?

26:58.750 --> 27:03.255
We gotta laugh with them
and make friends with them

27:03.288 --> 27:06.091
and meet their
goddamn families

27:06.125 --> 27:10.395
and then we just
tear them apart.

27:10.429 --> 27:12.131
Sometimes it's hard to tell

27:12.131 --> 27:14.666
whether they're the bad guys
or we are.

27:14.666 --> 27:19.371
Yeah.

27:19.404 --> 27:24.376
You know, the idea
of Graceland is great.

27:25.644 --> 27:28.447
You come home to good people,

27:28.480 --> 27:30.115
they keep you
on the straight path,

27:30.115 --> 27:34.453
but what if you're not
coming home to good people?

27:38.123 --> 27:41.994
You think Mike's right?

27:43.529 --> 27:45.664
I mean, I know Briggs would
move mountains to get Martun,

27:45.697 --> 27:50.335
but I just--I don't understand
why he would lie to us.

27:50.369 --> 27:52.538
And the shit Briggs does,

27:52.571 --> 27:56.475
half the time, I don't even know
what he's talking about.

27:59.978 --> 28:01.146
Vin. What are you doing out
here?

28:01.146 --> 28:02.548
- Waiting.
- Waiting for what?

28:02.548 --> 28:03.649
Take a big guess, Einstein.

28:03.682 --> 28:05.417
She locked me out.

28:05.450 --> 28:06.552
You here to score too?

28:06.552 --> 28:08.554
What, she's in there
with a dealer?

28:08.554 --> 28:10.422
Jesus Christ. Hey, Madison.

28:10.422 --> 28:11.356
It's Mike. Open up.

28:11.390 --> 28:12.424
How long she been in there?

28:12.424 --> 28:16.428
15 minutes.
Forever. Who cares?

28:16.428 --> 28:17.696
Hey, hey.

28:17.696 --> 28:19.565
What the hell is that?

28:19.598 --> 28:20.699
Mike.

28:20.699 --> 28:22.267
What the hell
are you doing, huh?

28:22.267 --> 28:24.236
What do you think?

28:24.269 --> 28:25.537
Hey, what is your problem?

28:25.537 --> 28:27.639
Hey, hey, be calm.
He's trying to help.

28:27.673 --> 28:29.508
You can't come in here
and tell me who my friends are.

28:29.541 --> 28:30.642
That's not your friend,
sweetheart.

28:30.676 --> 28:32.177
Who the hell are you?

28:32.177 --> 28:34.446
I'm Charlie and I'm gonna take
you somewhere, so get ready.

28:34.446 --> 28:36.315
Charlie, what are you,
pre-op or post-op, Charlie?

28:36.348 --> 28:38.317
Aw, we got a real
charmer here. Get ready.

28:38.350 --> 28:39.985
Yeah, up yours bitch,
I don't know you.

28:40.018 --> 28:42.654
No, you don't know me bitch,
so don't act like you do.

28:42.688 --> 28:43.689
Get off me.

28:43.722 --> 28:48.327
This isn't up for discussion.

28:48.360 --> 28:50.529
Get dressed.

28:54.066 --> 28:56.134
I'm going to file charges
against you, I hope you know.

28:56.168 --> 28:57.970
Unlawful entry,
assault and battery--

28:58.003 --> 29:00.639
Just shut up and watch.

29:05.544 --> 29:09.047
Hayley was born
with a vascular disorder.

29:09.081 --> 29:11.350
They amputated six months ago.

29:11.350 --> 29:13.719
She wakes up
every night crying,

29:13.752 --> 29:16.755
clutching something
that's not there.

29:16.755 --> 29:19.458
It's funny how the brain
wants to hold onto something

29:19.491 --> 29:21.627
that's gone.

29:21.660 --> 29:22.628
You think
you're the first person

29:22.661 --> 29:24.763
to spit
this psychobabble at me?

29:24.997 --> 29:27.633
I've had doctors,
nurses, shrinks,

29:27.633 --> 29:28.700
all saying to get over it.

29:28.734 --> 29:30.302
I would never say that.

29:30.335 --> 29:32.170
None of you know what it's like
to lose something, all right?

29:32.204 --> 29:33.472
So how bout you save me the--

29:33.505 --> 29:37.476
Don't talk about
what you don't know.

29:37.509 --> 29:40.045
I lost a child.

29:40.078 --> 29:41.313
Maybe it's not
the same as you,

29:41.346 --> 29:44.049
but it was a part of me
just the same.

29:44.082 --> 29:45.584
And I'll tell you,
when it happened,

29:45.617 --> 29:48.086
all I wanted to do was curl up
in a ball and disappear

29:48.120 --> 29:51.256
and go wherever it was
my baby went.

29:51.256 --> 29:55.093
- It's just not fair.
- No, it's not fair.

29:55.127 --> 29:57.195
Life's not fair.
None of it's fair.

29:57.229 --> 30:02.100
But if Hayley can stand up,
and learn to walk,

30:02.100 --> 30:05.370
and still have
a smile on her face,

30:05.370 --> 30:06.505
then you gotta be
a real asshole

30:06.505 --> 30:09.174
if you think
you've got it worse.

30:19.251 --> 30:22.187
[overlapping chatter,
shouting]

30:57.255 --> 30:58.690
That's right.

30:58.690 --> 31:01.393
Come in here knowing nothing,
that's how you get hurt, fool.

31:04.563 --> 31:07.165
Hey, yo.

31:07.165 --> 31:08.233
You wanna go a couple?

31:08.266 --> 31:10.102
[spits]
I don't know you, man.

31:10.135 --> 31:12.137
Oh, it's all good, man,
don't matter.

31:12.137 --> 31:14.406
I'm Johnny.
I'm from Long Beach--

31:14.439 --> 31:17.642
I said
I don't know you, homes.

31:17.676 --> 31:19.711
What's up man, I know
you ain't scared, right?

31:19.711 --> 31:22.547
I mean, you got all your
punk-ass boys right here.

31:22.581 --> 31:23.548
What you say?

31:23.582 --> 31:24.583
Couple rounds,
what's up?

31:24.616 --> 31:27.686
What you need,
a hearing aid?

31:27.719 --> 31:30.455
Look, I mean
no disrespect, bro.

31:30.455 --> 31:33.392
I just heard you were
someone I should talk to.

31:33.425 --> 31:37.729
I'm looking for work.
What's up?

31:37.763 --> 31:40.265
Look, I know you don't
know me and all,

31:40.298 --> 31:42.167
I just did a dime.

31:42.167 --> 31:44.703
In Chino. Armed robbery.

31:44.703 --> 31:49.441
Before that I ran with
Oscar Muñoz and Chico Moncado.

31:49.474 --> 31:51.543
[speaking Spanish]

31:51.576 --> 31:54.713
That's two dead men, homie.

31:54.713 --> 31:58.483
I did my time, man.
Now all I know is dead men.

31:58.483 --> 32:00.619
It's a sad story, dog.

32:00.619 --> 32:03.088
I'll take whatever you got, man.

32:03.121 --> 32:04.356
First one in, last man out.

32:04.356 --> 32:07.292
I ain't got shit to lose,
man, what's up?

32:07.325 --> 32:09.227
You want to do
something for me?

32:09.261 --> 32:12.063
Why don't you
get lost, homes.

32:12.097 --> 32:14.366
Punk.

32:14.366 --> 32:16.435
You win, I'll walk.

32:16.468 --> 32:21.039
You lose, we got business.

32:26.077 --> 32:28.480
[hisses]

32:28.480 --> 32:31.149
Come on.

32:31.183 --> 32:33.185
All right.

32:44.262 --> 32:46.031
[grunts]

33:07.652 --> 33:09.688
(man)
There we go.

33:12.290 --> 33:13.558
Hit 'em.

33:28.640 --> 33:32.043
- Whoa, whoa.
- Whoa.

34:03.441 --> 34:06.144
I just need a shot,
man, come on.

34:06.177 --> 34:09.147
Better get out of here
before I kill you.

34:31.436 --> 34:34.306
Get off me.

34:34.306 --> 34:37.108
Shit.

34:47.018 --> 34:47.464
[relaxed music]

34:49.754 --> 34:51.590
♪ ♪

34:51.623 --> 34:52.724
[door closes]

34:52.757 --> 34:54.326
(Jakes)
It's me. Who's home?

34:54.359 --> 34:55.727
Me.

34:55.760 --> 34:59.097
- Hey, lady.
- Hey.

34:59.097 --> 35:00.632
Christmas coming early
this year or what?

35:00.632 --> 35:03.435
Yeah, well they get
expensive in October

35:03.468 --> 35:05.570
so in the summer
you can get them cheaper.

35:05.604 --> 35:07.205
I learned that from my mama.

35:07.205 --> 35:10.075
Well, chocolate Santa
may have a little gift for you.

35:10.075 --> 35:12.611
Oh, yeah?

35:12.644 --> 35:14.412
I sold Germaine
on the meet and greet.

35:14.446 --> 35:16.147
- No.
- Yeah.

35:16.181 --> 35:17.449
We're gonna set something up
at the horse track

35:17.482 --> 35:18.583
in a couple days.

35:18.617 --> 35:20.352
- Jakes, thank you.
- Hold on, hold on.

35:20.385 --> 35:23.254
I still got to sweet talk the,
um, what did you call him again?

35:23.254 --> 35:25.223
- Master of weak ties.
- Master of weak ties, yeah.

35:25.256 --> 35:26.658
But it's a start.

35:26.658 --> 35:29.327
Wow. Tell me.

35:29.361 --> 35:32.597
Yeah, what the hell
happened here?

35:32.631 --> 35:34.399
I just talked to Charlie.

35:34.432 --> 35:35.967
She told me about the murder

35:35.967 --> 35:37.369
that occurred
in our living room.

35:37.369 --> 35:39.104
What the hell do you have
Paige going on, man?

35:39.137 --> 35:40.238
She asked on the case.

35:40.271 --> 35:41.706
Briggs, this is on you.

35:41.740 --> 35:43.208
She would not be on that case

35:43.241 --> 35:45.110
if you did not have her
on that case.

35:45.110 --> 35:47.312
This blood is on you.

35:47.345 --> 35:48.513
I need help.

35:48.546 --> 35:50.649
You serious?

35:50.649 --> 35:52.117
Listen to me.

35:52.150 --> 35:55.186
Even if I wanted to
help you, which I do not,

35:55.220 --> 35:57.389
I'm so busy with this case
with Charlie, man.

35:57.389 --> 35:59.224
- I'm flying back and forth--
- I'm not asking you--

35:59.257 --> 36:02.327
So then what
are you asking me?

36:02.360 --> 36:05.664
This, um,
money laundering bit.

36:05.697 --> 36:07.632
You could have millions
roll in if it goes right.

36:07.666 --> 36:08.667
What's your point?

36:08.700 --> 36:11.403
I need you
to peel me off some.

36:11.403 --> 36:13.238
You need me to peel you
off some?

36:13.271 --> 36:16.007
You need me to peel you
off some money

36:16.041 --> 36:18.977
from the federal investigation
that I'm working?

36:19.010 --> 36:20.679
- Do you hear yourself?
- Yes, I do.

36:20.712 --> 36:22.380
You boggle my mind, man.

36:22.414 --> 36:23.748
You boggle my mind, Briggs.

36:23.982 --> 36:26.484
This thing that I'm building
is a house of cards.

36:26.518 --> 36:29.487
If it falls, Dale,

36:29.521 --> 36:32.257
I'm not going to prison, man.

36:32.290 --> 36:34.392
You been in my shoes
before, remember?

36:34.426 --> 36:37.996
I feel like I paid that debt.

36:38.029 --> 36:41.166
I will never call
on this favor again.

36:41.199 --> 36:45.603
Never.

36:45.637 --> 36:47.672
How much are we talking?

36:47.706 --> 36:50.308
Enough to run away
and stay gone.

36:50.341 --> 36:54.279
Yeah.
Might be a good idea.

36:56.614 --> 36:59.050
[door slams]

36:59.084 --> 37:01.386
remember going
to summer camp.

37:01.419 --> 37:06.257
It was only two weeks,
but I cried like a baby.

37:06.291 --> 37:11.696
Yeah, maybe 30 days feel like
forever, but it's not so long.

37:11.730 --> 37:13.198
Hey, I'll throw these away.

37:13.198 --> 37:16.668
No, I got it.

37:16.701 --> 37:19.237
I gotta do it myself.

37:30.348 --> 37:32.317
Hey, maybe you want a ride
to the place.

37:32.350 --> 37:34.085
I'm happy to do it.

37:34.085 --> 37:36.321
No, to be honest,
I'm just going to call a cab.

37:36.354 --> 37:40.625
I just need to be alone.

37:40.625 --> 37:43.695
I'll see you
in a month, Gusti.

37:43.728 --> 37:46.231
It's Vin.

37:48.633 --> 37:50.135
Vin.

37:59.644 --> 38:01.312
She's gonna be all right.

38:01.346 --> 38:03.481
No, man, not all people
are good with change.

38:03.481 --> 38:05.316
Especially Madison.

38:05.350 --> 38:07.285
That's why we should always
stay with her, you know?

38:07.318 --> 38:08.586
Just help her settle in.

38:08.620 --> 38:10.388
Yeah.

38:10.388 --> 38:12.223
Hey, you still have
the phone?

38:12.257 --> 38:16.261
Yeah. Yeah.
I got it.

38:16.261 --> 38:20.131
Then maybe you want to sell
that thing in the box with me?

38:20.165 --> 38:21.599
You know I do.

38:21.633 --> 38:26.070
All right, so when it rings
we answer.

38:26.104 --> 38:27.372
Why'd you change your mind?

38:27.372 --> 38:30.208
Madison doesn't give up
on her life, why should I?

38:30.241 --> 38:31.242
Hey, thank you.

38:31.276 --> 38:33.378
- No, I--
- No, no, it was you, man.

38:33.378 --> 38:35.113
She would not make it
without you, okay?

38:35.113 --> 38:37.715
She'd be lost in her own head,
but you drag her out,

38:37.749 --> 38:39.083
you knew what she
needed to hear,

38:39.117 --> 38:42.987
and you put it
in front of her.

38:43.021 --> 38:46.024
What? What did I say?

38:48.126 --> 38:50.295
Son of a bitch.

38:54.032 --> 38:55.366
You made this for me?

38:55.400 --> 38:57.101
Put these all over
Gusti's building.

38:57.135 --> 38:59.137
You knew I'd see the birds.
You knew I'd call the number.

38:59.170 --> 39:00.271
You treated me like a mark.

39:00.271 --> 39:02.006
- Come on, man.
- You preyed on my weakness.

39:02.006 --> 39:03.641
I did not prey on anything,
Mike.

39:03.675 --> 39:06.144
Those little pills?
Those were your weakness.

39:06.144 --> 39:07.745
The birds were your strength.
I was trying to help you, man.

39:07.979 --> 39:09.480
I don't want to hear it, man.

39:09.514 --> 39:11.249
Every time, Paul.

39:11.282 --> 39:13.618
Every time I come at you,
you've got the right answer.

39:13.651 --> 39:15.386
No matter what it is,
you're always doing it

39:15.420 --> 39:16.621
for some noble cause.

39:16.654 --> 39:18.656
I got to tell you,
I don't buy it anymore.

39:18.690 --> 39:21.492
'Cause underneath the bullshit,
everything you do,

39:21.526 --> 39:24.696
you do it for yourself.

39:24.696 --> 39:27.632
[scoffs]

39:32.670 --> 39:37.108
Boss told you
to leave, eh?

39:37.141 --> 39:41.679
Oh, I thought he just
meant the ring, homie.

39:41.713 --> 39:45.283
Everything around here
belongs to me.

39:45.316 --> 39:47.252
And no one gets to come in here
and punk me.

39:47.285 --> 39:50.054
You think I'm
some kind of chump?

39:50.054 --> 39:53.057
No, brah, I don't think
you're a chump, man.

39:53.057 --> 39:57.695
I mean, a bitch for sure,
but not a chump.

39:57.729 --> 40:00.198
Hey, come on, fellas,
just chill, all right, man?

40:00.198 --> 40:03.167
[intense music]

40:03.167 --> 40:11.175
♪ ♪

40:27.625 --> 40:32.096
[door knocks]

40:32.096 --> 40:34.098
What do you want, man?

40:34.132 --> 40:36.067
I do everything you say.

40:36.067 --> 40:39.304
I even smile at your junkie
friend until he shoots me.

40:39.337 --> 40:41.606
When is it done?
When is it all finished?

40:41.606 --> 40:44.242
Soon.
